## Task

Write 3 platform-native social posts:

### 1. X (Twitter) Thread (4–6 tweets)
- Tweet 1: Hook tweet — attention-grabbing, shares the big problem or insight
- Tweet 2: Introduce the product — what it does + one standout feature
- Tweet 3–4: 2–3 specific features or use cases (one per tweet)
- Tweet 5: Social proof hook or milestone (placeholder if no real data: "[PLACEHOLDER]")
- Tweet 6 (optional): CTA tweet — link + call to action
- Each tweet ≤280 chars (hard limit)
- Include 1–3 relevant hashtags on the final tweet only

### 2. LinkedIn Post (long-form, 800–1,200 chars)
- Personal story hook (problem I/we faced)
- What we built (product + core benefit)
- 3 key features (brief bullets)
- Who it's for
- CTA + link
- Professional tone; paragraph breaks after every 2–3 lines

### 3. Show HN Post (Hacker News "Show HN")
- Format: "Show HN: [Product Name] – [one-liner description]"
- Body (200–400 words): technical background, motivation, what's interesting about the technical approach, honest limitations, what feedback you're looking for
- No marketing fluff; HN audience is technical; be honest and precise

**Rules:**
- Each tweet ≤280 chars
- ONLY mention features in the confirmed list
- CTA links: {{ live_url or "[PENDING_DEPLOY]" }}

